cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with preprocessing a directed planar graph with vertex labels and arc lengths into a data structure that answers distance queries. This involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions approximation algorithms (cs.DM) and the use of data structures for similarity search (cs.SI).
